sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant UI as Maestro Web UI / Mobile Browser
    participant API as FastAPI Backend
    participant Auth as Auth / Session Guard
    participant Maestro as Maestro Orchestrator
    participant Workflow as Maestro-Level Workflow<br/>(Daily Standup / Ideas / Status)
    participant Registry as Agent Registry
    participant Queue as Task Queue
    participant Agent as Domain Agent Service
    participant Tools as External Tools<br/>(Gmail, Calendar, GitHub, ClickUp, Web)
    participant Mem as Memory Service<br/>(Global, Domain, Agent)
    participant Curator as Memory Curator
    participant DB as Postgres
    participant Reports as Report Store

    User->>UI: Submit request to Maestro or selected agent
    UI->>API: POST /chat or /tasks
    API->>Auth: Validate user/session/domain access
    Auth-->>API: Authorized
    API->>Maestro: Create intent envelope
    Maestro->>Mem: Read relevant global + domain memory
    Mem->>DB: Query memories, summaries, policies, recent tasks
    DB-->>Mem: Context bundle
    Mem-->>Maestro: Scoped context
    Maestro->>Maestro: Decide direct answer, domain task, or Maestro-level workflow

    alt Maestro-level workflow
        Maestro->>Workflow: Start parent workflow task
        Workflow->>Registry: Identify domain brief agents and tools
        Registry-->>Workflow: Agent capabilities + tool permissions
        Workflow->>Workflow: Plan subordinate domain task(s)
    else Direct domain task
        Maestro->>Registry: Identify candidate agents and tools
        Registry-->>Maestro: Agent capabilities + tool permissions
        Maestro->>Maestro: Plan task(s), decide agent routing
    end

    alt Single-agent task
        Maestro->>Queue: Enqueue task for selected agent
    else Multi-agent task
        Maestro->>Queue: Enqueue tasks for multiple domain agents
    end

    Queue->>Agent: Dispatch task with scoped context
    Agent->>Mem: Read domain + agent memory
    Mem-->>Agent: Prior work, constraints, standing instructions
    Agent->>Tools: Execute approved tool calls
    Tools-->>Agent: Tool results
    Agent->>Agent: Analyze and produce structured report
    Agent->>Reports: Save report artifact
    Agent->>Mem: Write agent log + memory proposal
    Mem->>DB: Persist task log, report ref, memory proposal
    Mem->>Curator: Submit memory proposal + source refs
    Curator->>Curator: Classify impact and extract durable memory
    alt Low-impact memory
        Curator->>Mem: Write canonical memory
        Mem->>DB: Persist canonical memory + provenance links
    else Very high-impact memory
        Curator->>DB: Queue approval request
    end
    Agent-->>Queue: Task complete

    Queue-->>Maestro: Return agent report(s)
    Maestro->>Maestro: Synthesize cross-agent result
    Maestro->>Mem: Write synthesis log + memory proposal if needed
    Mem->>Curator: Submit synthesis memory proposal
    Maestro->>Reports: Save synthesis report
    Maestro-->>API: Final answer + report references + task status
    API-->>UI: Stream response/status updates
    UI-->>User: Display answer, reports, agent activity
